── D5: Persistent Homology scaffold ────────────────────────────────

── 1. Filtration value on smoothed GRF ─────────────────────────────

  σ_n²(R) = ∫ d³k/(2π)³  k^(2n) P(k) exp(−k²R²)

  Sublevel set:  X_ν = { x : φ_R(x) ≤ ν σ_0 }

  Vietoris-Rips radius at threshold ν (heuristic):
    r(ν) ≃ (σ_0 / σ_1) × √(2 ln(1/Φ(ν)))       [Φ = Gaussian CDF]

  <χ(ν)>_G (d=3, up to prefactor) ∝ (\nu**2 - 1)*exp(-\nu**2/2)

── 2. Leading fNL correction to <PH_k> at peak ─────────────────────

  Local fNL model:  φ(x) = φ_G(x) + fNL (φ_G² − <φ_G²>)

  H_3(ν) = \nu**3 - 3*\nu

  δ<χ(ν)>/⟨χ⟩_G  =  σ_0 · f_NL · H_3(ν) · S_3^prim / 6
  Leading form (S_3^prim absorbed): \nu*\sigma_0*f_{NL}*(\nu**2 - 3)*(\nu**2 - 1)*exp(-\nu**2/2)/2

  Peak shift:  <β_k(ν_*)>_NG = <β_k(ν_*)>_G · [1 + c_k fNL]
  Yip+24 (arXiv:2403.13985) Fig 5:  c_1 ≃ 2·10^−4 / fNL at R=10 Mpc/h

── LaTeX (paste into paper) ─────────────────────────────────────────
  \langle \beta_k(\nu_*) \rangle_{f_{NL}} = \langle \beta_k(\nu_*) \rangle_G \left[ 1 + c_k(\nu_*, R)\, f_{NL} \right]
  c_k \simeq \frac{\sigma_0(R)\, H_3(\nu_*)\, S_3^{\rm prim}(R)}{6}

